{
  "stem": "24814.2",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I was standing, talking to some of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They all spoke some German, and-- even though they were Poles and Russians and everything else.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They spoke enough German to get along by that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was talking to this one young Jew, and he kept talking to me between mouthfuls of bread, and he kept stroking me, saying, freunde, freunde, freunde.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Friends, friends, friends.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He couldn't believe we-- there we were, we were friends.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then he kept saying, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Mother, father, brother, sisters-- all burned, burned, burned.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then he tried to cry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "These people had no tear ducts.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They couldn't make tears.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] His chest would heave in these great sobs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[SIGHS] [GERMAN] Burned, burned.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That's all he could get out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Well, we went out to the rest of the camp and took the pictures that I'll show you later.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I was almost out of film, but I was lucky because the signal officer had lots of film, of course.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he had a Sergeant Lieberman, from New York-- Liebschitz, I think his name.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Liebschitz.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He was with us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They took some great pictures.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That's how-- we pooled pictures later on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We walked through the camp, and there were just dead bodies-- as you'll see, that you had to-- it was hard not to step on them, there so many dead bodies lying on the ground.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were just thick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, god, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the first-- it was an odor we knew pretty well, and that is when something is burned and rained on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first time you shell a town and move in, a lot of carca-- dead people, and dead animals, and they get burned and rained on.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
